          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-01-06 15:28:06" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to being morally corrupt and evil</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>immoral</Gloss>
                <Gloss>evil</Gloss>
                <Gloss>wicked</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In translating {S:04000501100022} it is important to indicate that the words spoken are not evil in themselves, but the content of what is spoken involves attributing evil and wicked deeds to the followers of Jesus. It may, therefore, be necessary to say in some languages ‘when men speak against you by saying that you have done wicked deeds.’</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
