          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-01-06 15:28:06" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to possessing a serious fault and consequently being worthless</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>bad</Gloss>
                <Gloss>worthless</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages one must speak of ‘bad fruit’ in the context of {S:04000701800012} as ‘fruit which does not taste good.’ It is often wrong to use an expression such as ‘rotten fruit,’ since a good tree may produce fruit which rots as a result of being overly ripe.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
